app.source.preprocessingDataset.PreprocessingControl module¶

preprocessing(userpath: str, userpathToPredict: str, prototypeSelection: bool, featureExtraction: bool, numRawsPS: int, numColsFE: int, doQSVM: bool)[source]¶

This function is going to preprocess a given Dataset with prototypeSelection or featureExtraction

Parameters

  • userpath – string that points to the location of the dataset to be preprocessed

  • prototypeSelection – boolean flag that indicated whether the user wants to execute a prototypeSelection or not

  • userpathToPredict – string that points to the location of the dataset to be predicted

  • featureExtraction – boolean flag that indicated whether the user wants to execute a feature Extraction or not

  • numRawsPS – number of rows the prototype selection should reduce the dataset to

  • numColsFE – number of columns the feature extraction should reduce the dataset to

  • doQSVM – boolean flag that indicated whether the user wants to execute classification or not

Returns

two preprocessed dataset: ‘DataSetTrainPreprocessato.csv’, ‘DataSetTestPreprocessato.csv’

Return type

(str, str)
